@startuml
' @id(DOM-DEPLOY-IAC)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
'
' Current-side domain model of the IaC artifact /mdd-deploy generates AND
' the execution that applies it, as implemented in
' templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL + .mdd/docs/deploy-profile.md.
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0021): the implemented skill no longer writes files and
' stops. Four execution concepts join the planning gates: RunbookExecution
' <<executor>>, DryRun <<gate>>, GoLiveGate <<gate>>, AuthContext
' <<principal>>. Stereotypes here are documentation-only; this file
' carries NO security-parity markers (/mdd-deploy is outside the gate).
'
' @desc(DOM-DEPLOY-IAC, "As implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL: /mdd-deploy generates IaC under two confirmed gates (DialectChoice, DeploymentPurpose) plus the ResourceAccess completeness gate, then EXECUTES it. After planning, a RunbookExecution (under an AuthContext the skill manages) applies the IaC: a DryRun must precede any apply (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-DRYRUN-BEFORE-APPLY), idempotent steps run autonomously while irreversible ones are confirmation-gated (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-PAUSE-IRREVERSIBLE), execution halts on the first failed step (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-HALT-ON-ERROR), and the GoLiveGate blocks the live-traffic cutover until the operator confirms the full billing multi-factor state (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-GOLIVE-CONFIRMED). BicepIaC and TerraformIaC compose the identical secured topology with the same secure-by-default + migration-order invariants.")
title /mdd-deploy generated IaC + execution (current)

class DialectChoice <<gate>> {
  value : {bicep | terraform}
  confirmed : Boolean
  rule = exactly one dialect per run
  rule = no artifact written until confirmed
  rule = no silent default
}

class DeploymentPurpose <<gate>> {
  value : {dev | staging | prod}
  confirmed : Boolean
  rule = no silent default (never assume dev- or prod-grade)
  rule = confirmed before any purpose-driven default
  drives = DB tier/redundancy, backup retention,
           RECOMMENDED network/doorway posture
  rule = RECOMMENDS only; operator confirms;
         secure-by-default vault posture preserved
}

class ResourceAccess <<gate>> {
  scope = every secured store (Key Vault, DB, ACR, remote state)
  reader = principal + identity + admitted path (runtime)
  writer = principal + identity + admitted path (provisioning)
  rule = read AND write both accounted for before "diagram done"
  rule = read-but-never-written => SURFACE blocking question
  rule = writer with no admitted path => SURFACE blocking question
  rule = surface the option (allowlist|in-VNet|tunnel); never bake one in
}

class Deployer <<principal>> {
  identity = operator or CI (whoever runs apply)
  role = Key Vault Secrets Officer (data-plane WRITE)
  reaches = vault over a network path the posture admits
}

class AuthContext <<principal>> {
  managedBy = the skill (runs az login + az account set)
  identity = the logged-in principal
  subscription = selected + verified before execution
  rule = wrong/ambiguous subscription => SURFACE and STOP
}

class RunbookExecution <<executor>> {
  walks = the generated runbook.md, step by step
  autonomous = idempotent/reversible steps (RG/ACR create, build, push, plan)
  gated = irreversible steps (first apply, secret writes, migration, go-live)
  rule = DRY-RUN must precede any apply
  rule = HALT on the first failed step (run no further step)
  rule = new revision at 0% traffic until health-checked
}

class DryRun <<gate>> {
  command = terraform plan / az deployment what-if
  rule = produced and shown before any apply
  rule = no apply runs without a prior dry-run
}

class GoLiveGate <<gate>> {
  scope = production billing multi-factor cutover + traffic routing
  surfaces = ENABLE_PRODUCTION_BILLING, APP_ENV, DATABASE_MARKER,
             PUBLIC_HOST, APPLE_ENVIRONMENT, App Attest prod identity
  rule = NEVER auto-confirmed; explicit operator confirmation required
  rule = the one stop full-auto never skips
}

abstract class IaCArtifact <<artifact>> {
  target = azure-container-apps (v1, only)
  generatedBy = /mdd-deploy (plan phase)
  appliedBy = RunbookExecution (the skill),
              operator-confirmed at irreversible steps
}
class BicepIaC <<artifact>> {
  language = Bicep (Azure-native ARM DSL)
  entrypoint = main.bicep
  appliedVia = az deployment
}
class TerraformIaC <<artifact>> {
  language = Terraform HCL
  entrypoint = main.tf
  provider = azurerm
  stateBackend = remote (azurerm backend)
  appliedVia = terraform plan + apply
}

class ContainerRegistry <<Azure ACR>>
class ContainerAppsEnv <<Azure Container Apps>>
class AppRevision <<Azure Container Apps>> {
  ingress = 8080 external
  user = non-root
  env = NODE_ENV=production
  rollout = 0% traffic until health-checked, then go-live cutover
}
class PostgresFlexibleServer <<Azure DB for PostgreSQL>> {
  transport = sslmode=require
  encryption = at-rest
  tier = set by DeploymentPurpose (surfaced, not assumed)
}
class KeyVault <<Azure Key Vault>> {
  holds = every secret (Container Apps secret refs)
  networkDefaultAction = Deny
  bypass = AzureServices
}
class AzureOpenAI <<Azure OpenAI>>
class MigrationJob <<Azure Container Apps Job>> {
  order = before any revision traffic routing
}

DialectChoice "1" --> "1" IaCArtifact : selects & gates
DeploymentPurpose "1" --> "1" IaCArtifact : sizes & postures (recommends)
IaCArtifact <|-- BicepIaC
IaCArtifact <|-- TerraformIaC

RunbookExecution "1" --> "1" AuthContext : runs under
RunbookExecution "1" --> "1" DryRun : must precede apply
RunbookExecution "1" --> "1" GoLiveGate : blocks live cutover
RunbookExecution "1" ..> "1" IaCArtifact : applies

IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" ContainerRegistry
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" ContainerAppsEnv
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" KeyVault
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" PostgresFlexibleServer
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" AzureOpenAI
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" MigrationJob
ContainerAppsEnv "1" *-- "1..*" AppRevision
AppRevision ..> ContainerRegistry : pull image
AppRevision ..> KeyVault : secret refs <<Secrets User>> (runtime READ)
AppRevision ..> PostgresFlexibleServer : <<Encrypt>> TLS (sslmode=require)
AppRevision ..> AzureOpenAI : API key (landmine: NOT managed identity)
MigrationJob ..> PostgresFlexibleServer : <<Encrypt>> schema migrate
MigrationJob "1" --> "1" AppRevision : completes BEFORE\ntraffic routing

Deployer ..> KeyVault : set secrets <<Secrets Officer>> (provisioning WRITE)
ResourceAccess "1" --> "1" KeyVault : completeness check (exemplar)
GoLiveGate "1" --> "1" AppRevision : gates traffic cutover

note bottom of RunbookExecution
  The execution engine (CMP-DEPLOY-EXEC). Walks the runbook
  via Bash (az/terraform/docker). Idempotent steps run
  AUTONOMOUSLY; irreversible steps and go-live are
  confirmation-gated; execution HALTS on the first failed
  step. Invariants: OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-HALT-ON-ERROR,
  OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-PAUSE-IRREVERSIBLE.
end note

note bottom of DryRun
  A plan/what-if must run and be shown before ANY apply.
  Invariant: OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-DRYRUN-BEFORE-APPLY.
end note

note bottom of GoLiveGate
  The one stop full-auto never skips: surfaces the full
  production billing multi-factor state, then BLOCKS for
  explicit operator confirmation before the live-traffic
  cutover. Never auto-confirmed. Invariant:
  OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-GOLIVE-CONFIRMED.
end note

note bottom of KeyVault
  Secure-by-default, identical for BOTH dialects: when
  Postgres + Azure OpenAI are private, Key Vault is
  generated with networkAcls.defaultAction='Deny' +
  bypass='AzureServices'. Invariant:
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SECURE-BY-DEFAULT.
end note

note bottom of IaCArtifact
  FULL PARITY: BicepIaC and TerraformIaC compose the same
  secured topology and satisfy the same invariant checklist.
  Produced by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE; written into
  CMP-DEPLOY-TARGET; APPLIED by RunbookExecution via
  SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE. Constrained by
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SECURE-BY-DEFAULT / -MIGRATION-ORDER.
end note
@enduml
